{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","id":"msg_011CdH7vwcoAJzDEDkUqVqKy","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Fixed. Tests pass.\n\n**Root cause:** The cache key in `getUsers` (`src/userService.js:10`) was built only from `opts.team`, so it ignored `opts.includeArchived`. When something requested a team's users *with* archived users included, that list got cached under `users:<team>`. The next normal picker call for the same team hit that cache entry and got archived users back — even though it never asked for them. The 60s TTL is why refreshing after a minute clears it: the stale entry expires and the correct query runs.\n\n**Fix:** Include the `includeArchived` flag in the cache key, so archived-inclusive and active-only results are cached separately:\n\n```js\nconst key = `users:${opts.team}:${opts.includeArchived ? \"all\" : \"active\"}`;\n```\n\nThe existing test suite (`test/cache.test.js`) passes."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":317,"cache_read_input_tokens":23440,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":317},"output_tokens":2,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"916e69f0-50b6-4d26-ac0f-5f0173fc12b2","uuid":"03bcb4cc-c537-4983-b900-78ba4cc72ba1","timestamp":"2026-07-22T12:46:58.477Z","request_id":"req_011CdH7vv9VfR2LbBudsqVz8"}
